  "summary": "rust-openssl: Unchecked callback length in PSK/cookie trampolines leaks adjacent memory to peer",
  "details": "The FFI trampolines behind `SslContextBuilder::set_psk_client_callback`, `set_psk_server_callback`, `set_cookie_generate_cb`,  and `set_stateless_cookie_generate_cb` forwarded the user closure's returned usize directly to OpenSSL without checking it against the `\u0026mut [u8]` that was handed to the closure. This can lead to buffer overflows and other unintended consequences.",
